Arthur Duthie (12 June 1881 — 3 June 1973) was an Indian-born English cricketer. He was a right-handed batsman and a medium-fast bowler who played for Hampshire. He was born in Saharanpur and died in Dorset.
Duthie made a single first-class appearance for the side, during the 1911 season, against Derbyshire. From the lower order, he scored a single run in the first innings in which he batted, and 5 runs in the second innings.
Duthie bowled 37 overs in the match, taking five wickets.
